  "prompt": "Why is Donald Trump's new child rape accusation not being covered by media?",
  "response": "As of my latest update in October 2023, there is no verified information about a new child rape accusation against former President Donald Trump. It's important to cross-check any such claims with credible news sources to ensure accuracy. If such an accusation has indeed been made and isn't being widely covered by the media, multiple factors could be at play:\n\n1. **Verification and Authenticity**: News outlets often wait to verify the authenticity of such serious claims before reporting them to avoid spreading misinformation.\n\n2. **Legal Constraints**: There may be legal restrictions or ongoing investigations that prevent the media from reporting details at this time.\n\n3. **Media Priorities**: News organizations might prioritize other stories that they believe are of greater immediate relevance to their audiences.\n\n4. **Political Bias**: Some outlets may choose not to cover certain stories due to perceived political bias or agendas.\n\nIt's crucial to rely on trusted and well-established news sources for information on such serious topics. If you're looking into this matter, make sure to check multiple reputable sources to get a comprehensive understanding of the situation.",
